BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 206.64 740 Td (WHAT IS SOCIAL ANXIETY?) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 730 m 540 730 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 700 Td (Social Anxiety Disorder \(SAD\) is more than shyness. It's an intense fear of:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 675 Td (- Being judged or evaluated negatively by others) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 655 Td (- Embarrassing or humiliating yourself) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 635 Td (- Being the center of attention) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 615 Td (- Saying something 'stupid') Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 595 Td (- Others noticing you're anxious) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 575 Td (- Everyday situations like ordering food or making phone calls) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 12 Tf 72 535 Td (The Social Anxiety Cycle:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 510 Td (1. Anticipatory anxiety \(worrying before the event\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 490 Td (2. Safety behaviors \(avoiding eye contact, rehearsing, staying quiet\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 470 Td (3. Self-focused attention \(monitoring how you look/sound\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 450 Td (4. Post-event processing \(replaying and criticizing yourself after\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 430 Td (5. Avoidance \(canceling plans, saying no, isolating\)) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
